e;color:#d40000;">covered</a> the story in 2020 (I worked there at the time=
, but wasn=E2=80=99t involved in the article)<em>,
</em>leading to a defamation lawsuit by Middleton against <em>THR</em> for =
portraying him as a drunk. Covering all his bases, Middleton also sued his =
sobriety coaches for overbilling him and supplying him with booze. (The law=
suit against <em>THR</em> eventually fizzled.)</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">As with most scandals, the=
 furor eventually dimmed, and the legal tussle between Middleton and Lee sl=
owed down after Middleton=E2=80=99s billionaire father tried
to cut off access to his trust fund. It was all but forgotten by the time a=
 judge ruled, in July 2022, that a jury would have to decide Middleton=E2=
=80=99s claim that Lee falsely promised producer credits in exchange for mo=
re than $7 million in benefits.</p></div>
